    • map

      public static <T, R> R @Nonnull [] map(T @Nonnull [] source, R @Nonnull @OutParam [] dest, @Nonnull @Nonnull Function<? super T,? extends R> mapper)
      Maps the source array to the dest array by specified mapper.

      If the dest array's length equals to the source array's length, the dest array will be returned. Otherwise, a new array with same length of the source array will be created and returned.

      Each element of the source array will be mapped to a new element by the specified mapper, then be set into the result array at corresponding index.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the component type of the source array
      R - the component type of the dest array
      Parameters:
      source - the source array
      dest - the dest array
      mapper - the specified mapper
      Returns:
      the given dest or a new result array

    • map

      public static <T, R> R @Nonnull [] map(T @Nonnull [] source, @Nonnull @Nonnull Function<? super T,? extends R> mapper) throws UnsupportedOperationException
      Maps the source array to the dest array by the specified mapper.

      This method tries to create a new array to receive the mapping result and return. Each element of the source array will be mapped to a new element by the specified mapper, then be set into the created new array at corresponding index. The component type of the new array is the type of the first nonnull new element. If all new elements are null, an UnsupportedOperationException will be thrown.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the component type of the source array
      R - the component type of the dest array
      Parameters:
      source - the source array
      mapper - the specified mapper
      Returns:
      a new result array
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - if all new elements are null
